  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "m77jqaWTvyVtaKWRKSxs8OFt/CA=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Feed Topic Naming Convention (ph:v2:*)\n\nThe adapter uses a versioned colon-delimited topic namespace for all Swarm feeds. The `ph:v2:` prefix anchors the schema version and enables forward-compatible migration.\n\n| Feed | Topic pattern | Content |\n|------|--------------|---------|\n| Document manifest | `ph:v2:doc:<documentId>` | Pointer to encrypted operation batches |\n| Drive manifest | `ph:v2:drive:<driveId>` | Documents + folder structure for one drive |\n| User manifest | `ph:v2:user:<eth_address>` | Index of all user's drives |\n| Public profile | `ph:v2:profile:<address>` | Bee node public key for sharing (unencrypted) |\n| Share manifest | `ph:v2:share:<sender>:<recipient>` | Shared drive bundles between users |\n\nTopology is hierarchical: **user manifest \u2192 drive manifests \u2192 document manifests \u2192 encrypted op batches**. On recovery, a client reads the user feed first, then descends to discover all drives and documents.\n\nProfile feeds are the only unencrypted feeds \u2014 they publish a Bee node's public key so senders can ACT-encrypt shares to that recipient. Share feeds carry full drive bundles (including folder metadata) from sender to recipient.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
